claim.claim-text:
A scheduling method, comprising the steps of:
selecting subcarriers from a plurality of subcarriers within predetermined communication band;
measuring channel quality for the selected subcarriers;
reporting channel quality information to a communicating party, the channel quality information being information of the measured channel quality for the subcarriers; and
selecting at the communicating party, subcarriers to which a transmission signal is allocated, based on the channel quality information;
characterized by
selecting subcarriers to which the data is to be allocated, when data whose allowable delay time is equal to or greater than a predetermined period is transmitted from the communicating party; and
selecting subcarriers such that the number of subcarriers to which data is allocated decreases in accordance with an increase in the allowable delay time of the data.
